main event: Multiple radar sightings of unidentified flying objects were reported over Lackland AFB, Texas on 25 May 1953. The objects appeared as unnatural sights and remained consistent in size and speed.
interesting points: Radar contact was made with five or more targets, which appeared to be orbiting over the base for 15 to 20 minutes.
Photographs were taken with scope cameras, but the film revealed camera damage.
A possible weather inversion was mentioned as a potential cause of the radar sightings.
Radar contact was intermittent and maintained for over 20,000 ft with no speed estimates possible.
The sightings were described as possibly caused by large government aircraft or small groups of bombers.
sighted object: unidentified flying objects detected by radar
photographs: scope camera photographs were attempted but revealed camera damage
